						               													<description>1930. A thousand oligarchic families own &amp;quot;La Argentina&amp;quot; and manage the State as part of their properties, making all kinds of deals and looting of the national treasury. In this decade, electoral and economic fraud, repression of popular sovereignty and abuses of power of all kinds are the order of the day.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To carry out its negotiations, the Argentine Oligarchy uses collaborators of the same kind. It is precisely there, where our players come into play...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;OBJECTIVE OF THE GAME&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The representative of the thousand families delegates his affairs to the first player next to the loot box, which is passed from hand to hand around the table. Each player takes advantage of the opportunity to get hold of the deals that he contains for individual benefit, or to take a character token with whom he collaborates.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After the round and with the box again in possession of the representative of the Argentine Oligarchy, he sees that some of his peers have cheated the interest of the ruling class for personal gain. Immediately afterwards he -offended and betrayed- he interrogates them to identify his henchmen trying to discover who or who have &amp;quot;abusers of his trust&amp;quot; and thus be able to recover his businesses for the set of the thousand oligarchic families. But if the deadline is met, if the Argentine Oligarchy has not managed to recover all the negotiations, it loses the game and the Prosecutors of the Homeland win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Will the Argentine oligarchy be able to recover all the stolen contracts? Will he take a false step by accusing a National Prosecutor in vain? What will be the fate of the thieves if the oligarchy falls? What luck will the Ruffians have with the different outcomes? A game of simulation and deception where each group of interests will want to win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
